    "Evaluation": {
      "text": "Usually clinical diagnosis\nIf associated exudative pharyngitis, consider Rapid GAS testing\nIf severe symptoms (ill-appearing, high fever), consider:\nBasic labs (CBC, BMP)\nBlood cultures\nESR/CRP may be helpful for monitoring course of infection/response to treatment\nUltrasound to evaluate for associate abscess or deep locations\nIf subacute/chronic, consider:\nCBC, BMP, ESR/CRP\nUric acid, LDH\nTuberculin skin test",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": []
    },
    "Management": {
      "text": "Mild symptoms (well appearing, absent/low-grade fever, minimal tenderness)\nSerial exams, PMD follow-up\nPO Antibiotic treatment if associated GAS pharyngitis found\nModerate symptoms (fever, tenderness without fluctuance)\nEmpiric PO Antibiotic therapy that covers S. Aureus and GAS\nCephalexin\n500 mg PO QID x 10 days\nAmoxicillin-Clavulanate\n875 mg PO BID x 10 days\nClindamycin\n300-450 mg PO TID x 10 days\nConsider anaerobic coverage if found to have poor dentition or evidence of periodontal disease\nSevere symptoms (ill-appearing, fever, fluctuance or overlying cellulitis)\nIncision & Drainage or Needle Aspiration\nIV Antibiotics",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": [
        {
          "text": "Cephalexin",
          "url": "https://wikem.org/wiki/Cephalexin"
        },
        {
          "text": "Amoxicillin-Clavulanate",
          "url": "https://wikem.org/wiki/Amoxicillin-Clavulanate"
        },
        {
          "text": "Clindamycin",
          "url": "https://wikem.org/wiki/Clindamycin"
        }
      ]
    },
    "Disposition": {
      "text": "Generally can be discharged with outpatient follow-up/treatment if mild/moderate symptoms\nAdmit for:\nSepsis\n/Severe symptoms requiring I&D or IV antibiotics\nFailure of outpatient treatment",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": [
